OL,3,CConservative MP Mark Logan defects to
OL,4,CLabour
OL,6,FMr Logan won his seat from Labour in
OL,7,Fthe 2019 general election with a
OL,8,Fnarrow majority of just 378, making it
OL,9,Fone of the most marginal in the
OL,10,Fcountry.
OL,12,FHe was a junior member of the
OL,13,FGovernment, a parliamentary private
OL,14,Fsecretary to ministers in the
OL,15,FDepartment for Work and Pensions.
OL,17,FHe becomes the third Tory to defect to
OL,18,FLabour since late April, following Dan
OL,19,FPoulter and Natalie Elphicke. Bury
OL,20,FSouth MP Christian Wakeford defected
OL,21,Fin January 2022.
